          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA",
                "EXTB",
                "MOMIX",
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The incident Ca-48 ion beam was grazed the lateral face",
                "of a rotating hollow cylinder. This surface  was",
                "covered by a thin (about 2-mg/cm**2) layer of the",
                "target material deposited by vacuum vaporization. In",
                "this geometry the target is considered to be",
                " infinitely  thick for the ion beam and recoil  nuclei",
                "and, at the same time, sufficiently thin for an",
                "efficient detection of the fragment of spontaneously",
                "fissioning reaction products. Thus the cylinder",
                "surface served both as a target and a recoil catcher.",
                "The cylinder rotation transported the nuclei to Mica",
                "fission  track  detectors  placed  along  the  cylinder",
                "surface, and set a time scale for measuring spontaneous",
                "fission half-lives. During the  experiments,  the  ion",
                "beam  intensity  was  controlled  by  a  special device",
                "placed outside the target. The integral ion  beam  was",
                "determined  using an activation analysis method, namely",
                "from the build-up of a long-lived  activity  in  an",
                "aluminium  sample  occupying a small  fraction of the",
                "working surface of the rotating cylinder."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". The detection efficiency was about 50%."
              ]
